# HarnessFlow on Cursor

This workspace ships HarnessFlow: a three-layer skill suite for spec-driven (SDD) + test-driven (TDD) development with pluggable domain extensions.

## On every development task

1. Load `skills/hf-workflow/SKILL.md` first. It defines the main chain `specify → review → design → review → tdd → review → ship`, the artifact layout under `features/<NNN>-<slug>/`, and how to recover the current stage from on-disk artifacts.
2. Follow the skill for the current stage: `hf-specify`, `hf-design`, `hf-review`, `hf-tdd`, `hf-ship` — read the stage skill's `SKILL.md` when you enter that stage.
3. Before each stage, check `skills/ext-*/` descriptions and load extensions whose binding stage and trigger conditions match.

## Hard rules

- Do not skip stage gates: a stage artifact must pass `hf-review` (and user confirmation in `interactive` mode) before the next stage starts.
- Author/reviewer separation: whoever wrote an artifact must not approve it — dispatch an independent review per `hf-review`.
- One task at a time in the tdd stage; no implementation code before a failing test.
- Recover state from `features/<NNN>-<slug>/` artifacts, not chat memory.

Pure Q&A or code-reading requests that produce no code changes do not need HarnessFlow.
